60|$|I {{perceived}} {{that she was}} not listening. There was no mistaking her expression; and once more I had the sense of being out of it--not because of my age, which at any rate could draw inferences--but altogether out of it, on another plane whence <b>I</b> could only <b>watch</b> <b>her</b> from afar. And so ceasing to speak <b>I</b> <b>watched</b> <b>her</b> stepping out by my side.|$|R
60|$|On Midsummer-eve, Adele, weary with {{gathering}} wild strawberries in Hay Lane {{half the}} day, {{had gone to}} bed with the sun. <b>I</b> <b>watched</b> <b>her</b> drop asleep, and when I left her, I sought the garden.|$|R
60|$|<b>I</b> <b>watched</b> <b>her</b> all {{the evening}} and the queer feeling in me somewhere grew worse and worse. I couldn't eat anything. Sidney took Mrs. Rennie in; they sat {{opposite}} to me and talked all the time.|$|R
